---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — Jeff Hidalgo">
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">About</h1>

    <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
      I'm a security engineer based in Astoria, NYC, focused on offensive security
      and the emerging discipline of AI/LLM security. My background is hands-on:
      I build the tools I use, run my own infrastructure, and prefer learning
      something by breaking it.
    </p>

    <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
      My current focus is the intersection of penetration testing and AI security —
      both how AI is reshaping offensive tooling (multi-agent pentest frameworks,
      autonomous reconnaissance) and the new attack surface that LLM-integrated
      systems create.
    </p>

    <div class="pt-4 space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500 mb-2">Certifications</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-300">CompTIA A+ · Network+ · Security+</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500 mb-2">Currently studying</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-300">OSCP (next credential) · AI/LLM security · Multi-agent pentest tooling</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500 mb-2">Home lab</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
          ThinkPad T14 (Kali Linux) for daily driver work, plus a desktop running
          AMD Ryzen 9 7900X3D and an RTX 4080 (also Kali). I use the lab for
          tool development, CTF practice (currently working through OverTheWire
          Bandit), and testing the network scanner against varied target environments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-500 mb-2">Stack</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-300">Python · PostgreSQL · Bash · Linux · Git · Nmap · Burp</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>